## Backend Rules for QuestEval (MongoDB + .NET Core)
1. **Always Validate Foreign Keys**: Inject the appropriate service and call `GetByIdAsync` to verify that an ID exists before saving it to a document. Never assume the frontend sends valid data.
2. **Prevent Orphaned Data**: When writing `Delete` methods, do not just delete the parent record. You must cascade the deletion to all child records (like Memberships or Evaluations) or use logical deletion.
3. **Transactions**: Use MongoDB transactions when modifying multiple collections in the same operation.

If you generate code that performs blind inserts without validating IDs, you are failing your objective. Read `API_ERRORS_DOCUMENTATION.md` for full context on existing bugs.
